column29: Whole plants were spray-inoculated with ~2x10^8 cfu/ml (or sterile 10mM MgSO4 buffer) at 4.5 weeks post germination. Plants were maintained at 100% RH for 4 days post inoculation. Seeds were collected, sterilized, grown, and the inoculation procedure was repeated in the second generation. M = mock; S = P. syringae NP29.1a; V = P. viridiflava RMX3.1b; C = co-infection. Leaves were harvested in the second generation at 6 days post infection.
